								</ul>
							</div>

							<div class="callout">
								<strong>These do not stack infinitely ‚Äî only 1 pack upgrade may be worn.</strong>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div id="dropping-gear" class="subsection">
							<h3>Dropping Gear Rules</h3>

							<h4>‚öî Dropping a held or carried item:</h4>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Fast Action</strong></li>
							</ul>

							<h4>Retrieving a dropped item:</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Move into space</li>
								<li><strong>Fast Action to pick up</strong></li>
							</ul>

							<h4>Re-equipping stored Gear:</h4>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Action</strong></li>
							</ul>

							<div class="callout">
								This prevents infinite swapping mid-fight.
							</div>

							<h4>üî• Edge Case Clarifications</h4>

							<div class="example-box">
								<p><strong>1Ô∏è‚É£ Can you carry 6 weapons?</strong></p>
								<p>Yes ‚Äî but no room for armor or tools.</p>

								<p><strong>2Ô∏è‚É£ Can you carry multiple armor sets?</strong></p>
								<p>Yes ‚Äî but each consumes a Gear Slot.</p>

								<p><strong>3Ô∏è‚É£ Can traps be pre-set without carrying them?</strong></p>
								<p>Yes ‚Äî if crafted earlier and placed.</p>

								<p><strong>4Ô∏è‚É£ Can you exceed slots temporarily?</strong></p>
								<p>Yes ‚Äî but penalties apply immediately.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</section>

					<!-- SURVIVAL & BIOMES -->
					<section id="survival-biomes" class="major-section">
						<h2 class="section-title">Survival & Biomes</h2>

						<div class="intro-box">
							<p>Survival systems exist to:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Add pressure between combats</li>
								<li>Reward preparation</li>
								<li>Make the world feel alive</li>
								<li>Change how hunts unfold</li>
							</ul>
							<p><strong>They are not meant to slow play with bookkeeping.</strong></p>
						</div>

						<div id="sector-movement" class="subsection">
							<h3>Sector Movement</h3>

							<p>Biomes are divided into <strong>Sectors</strong>.</p>

							<p>A sector represents:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>A distinct terrain space</li>
								<li>A combat arena</li>
								<li>A resource zone</li>
								<li>A narrative shift</li>
							</ul>

							<p>Movement between sectors is <strong>narrative, not grid-based</strong>.</p>

							<h4>Sectors change when:</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>A monster flees</li>
								<li>Hunters pursue</li>
								<li>Hunters retreat</li>
								<li>Environmental events trigger</li>
							</ul>

							<h4>Entering a new sector may reveal:</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Hazards</li>
								<li>Resource nodes</li>
								<li>Environmental modifiers</li>
								<li>Weather changes</li>
								<li>New tactical terrain</li>
							</ul>

							<div class="callout">
								<strong>That's all you need. Do not over-mechanize this.</strong>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div id="hazards" class="subsection">
							<h3>Hazards</h3>

							<p>Hazards are where mechanics matter.</p>

							<h4>1Ô∏è‚É£ Terrain Hazards</h4>

							<p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Swamp</strong> ‚Üí Difficult Terrain</li>
								<li><strong>Cliff Edge</strong> ‚Üí Fall risk</li>
								<li><strong>Ice</strong> ‚Üí Balance checks</li>
								<li><strong>Dense Canopy</strong> ‚Üí Reduced visibility</li>
							</ul>

							<p><strong>Resolution:</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li>DEX / Athletics / Acrobatics vs DC 10‚Äì14 depending on severity.</li>
							</ul>

							<p><strong>Failure results in:</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li>Prone</li>
								<li>Movement loss</li>
								<li>Minor damage</li>
								<li>Stamina loss</li>
							</ul>

							<div class="callout">
								<strong>Keep consequences tactical ‚Äî not lethal.</strong>
							</div>

							<h4>2Ô∏è‚É£ Environmental Hazards</h4>

							<p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li>Extreme Heat</li>
								<li>Freezing Winds</li>
								<li>Acid Rain</li>
								<li>Spore Clouds</li>
								<li>Volcanic Vents</li>
							</ul>

							<p><strong>Resolution:</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li>Usually CON save DC 12‚Äì16</li>
							</ul>

							<p><strong>Failure causes:</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li>Stamina loss</li>
								<li>Exhaustion gain</li>
								<li>Status condition</li>
							</ul>

							<div class="callout">
								<strong>These create pressure dials.</strong>
							</div>

							<h4>3Ô∏è‚É£ Monster-Triggered Hazards</h4>

							<p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li>Cave collapse</li>
								<li>Flooded chamber</li>
								<li>Burning forest</li>
								<li>Predators drawn to scent</li>
							</ul>

							<p><strong>These happen when:</strong></p>
							<ul>
